report_metadata.report_title: Work Integrated Learning (WIL) Data Analysis Report

year_comparison.title: Faculty Enrollment Overview (2025)
year_comparison.description: This chart displays the distribution of WIL students across 9 faculties. A total of 10,776 students are enrolled in WIL programs.
year_comparison.key_finding: The largest faculty by enrollment is Faculty of Engineering.

faculty_residency.title: Student Distribution by Faculty and Residency Status
faculty_residency.description: This grouped bar chart compares local and international student enrollment across different faculties, providing insights into the diversity and international appeal of each program.
faculty_residency.key_finding: Overall, 57.1% are local students and 42.3% are international students.

gender_distribution.title: Gender Representation Analysis
gender_distribution.description: These charts examine gender balance across the WIL program, showing both overall distribution and faculty-specific gender ratios to identify areas for diversity improvement.
gender_distribution.key_finding: Gender information is not available in the WIL dataset.

program_overview: The WIL program serves 10,776 students across 9 faculties.
A total of 181 different courses are offered.
The program demonstrates strong diversity in both academic disciplines and student demographics.
diversity_analysis: Gender information is not available in WIL data.
